Here's a comprehensive list of Terraform commands (CLI), organized by category.

Main Workflow

terraform init — initialize working directory (download providers/modules, configure backend)
terraform validate — check config syntax/consistency
terraform plan — preview changes
terraform apply — apply changes
terraform destroy — destroy managed infrastructure
terraform fmt — format config files to canonical style
State Management

terraform state list — list resources in state
terraform state show — show a resource's attributes
terraform state mv — move/rename a resource in state
terraform state rm — remove a resource from state (without destroying)
terraform state pull — output remote state to stdout
terraform state push — overwrite remote state from local
terraform state replace-provider — change provider for resources
terraform force-unlock — manually release a stuck state lock
Inspection / Output

terraform show — show state or a saved plan (human/JSON)
terraform output — read output values
terraform graph — generate dependency graph (DOT format)
terraform console — interactive expression evaluation
terraform providers — show provider requirements
terraform providers schema — provider schemas (JSON)
terraform providers lock — update .terraform.lock.hcl
terraform providers mirror — mirror providers locally
terraform version — show version + provider versions
Resource Lifecycle / Targeting

terraform apply -replace=ADDR — replace a resource (modern taint)
terraform plan/apply -target=ADDR — operate on specific resources
terraform apply -refresh-only — sync state with real infra (modern refresh)
terraform taint — mark resource for recreation (deprecated → -replace)
terraform untaint — remove taint mark (deprecated)
terraform refresh — update state (deprecated → -refresh-only)
Import

terraform import ADDR ID — import existing infra into state
Modules

terraform get — download/update modules
Workspaces

terraform workspace new — create a workspace
terraform workspace select — switch workspace
terraform workspace list — list workspaces
terraform workspace show — show current workspace
terraform workspace delete — delete a workspace
Testing (1.6+)

terraform test — run .tftest.hcl test files
Terraform Cloud / Enterprise

terraform login — obtain/store API token
terraform logout — remove stored credentials
Common Flags

-auto-approve — skip interactive approval (apply/destroy)
-var 'name=value' / -var-file=file.tfvars — set variables
-out=planfile — save plan to a file
-target=ADDR — limit to specific resources
-replace=ADDR — force replacement
-refresh-only — only refresh state
-refresh=false — skip refresh
-lock=false / -lock-timeout=DURATION — state locking control
-parallelism=n — concurrent operations (default 10)
-json — machine-readable output
-no-color — disable colored output
-input=false — disable interactive prompts (CI use)
-compact-warnings — condensed warnings
-detailed-exitcode — plan exit codes (0=no change, 1=error, 2=changes)
OpenTofu equivalent

All commands above work as tofu <command> (e.g., tofu init, tofu plan, tofu apply) in the OpenTofu fork.
That's the full set of built-in Terraform CLI commands plus the most-used flags. Day-to-day work is mostly init → plan → apply, with state, import, and -target/-replace for surgical operations.